  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CFD hemolysis credibility assessment (CPB)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML-augmented CFD hemolysis prediction pipeline applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. A feedforward neural network surrogate (3 hidden layers, 128 units each, ReLU activations) was trained on CFD-generated shear-stress exposure histories to predict the relative hemolysis index (RH) across the 5 flow-speed operating points. COU1 evaluates whether the combined CFD+ML model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Reproducibility of the neural network surrogate was studied informally during development; no quantitative characterisation of seed-to-seed variance is reported in this package.",
